<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCA BUYOUT BY JAPANESE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I would not worry about the sale of an American business to Japan. 
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has plenty of foreign ownership all over Europe and elsewhere. 
</P>
<P>
On my recent trip to France, I tried to buy some children's T-shirts with 
French writing on them. They were impossible to find but everywhere I found 
T-shirts from the U.S. Jeans, grocery products, cosmetics, etc. from America 
were available everywhere. 
</P>
<P>
I must admit, they love everything American. Now it is our turn: Can we learn 
to love Japanese entertainment? 
</P>
<P>
YVETTE CARR, Glendora 
</P>
