<HEADLINE>
<P>
COST OF WAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush has given us some good reasons to go to war against Iraq. 
</P>
<P>
Yet Washington, Lincoln and Roosevelt might have told us that good reasons are 
not good enough. For war you need overwhelming reasons. And considering the 
price of war, even overwhelming reasons are just barely good enough. 
</P>
<P>
TOM ANDRES, Santa Barbara 
</P>
