NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
NATIONWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
WEATHER FORECAST FAILURES REPORTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The National Weather Service has fallen short of its mission to warn the public 
of savage weather that claims more than 400 lives and causes $6 billion in 
damage every year, a newspaper reported. The federal agency misses two-thirds 
of all tornadoes, three-fifths of all flash floods and 40% of severe 
thunderstorms every year, the Cleveland Plain Dealer said. The newspaper said 
its investigation was based on weather service internal computer records and 
other data. 
</P>
