</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
East Los Angeles College became the first undefeated state junior college men's 
soccer champion when it downed Moorpark, 1-0, in the final match Sunday at 
Chabot College in Hayward. 
</P>
<P>
The teams played through a scoreless first half before Julio Umana scored the 
match's only goal with less than 10 minutes remaining. 
</P>
<P>
He picked up a pass from Adolfo Carranza, dribbled into the penalty area and 
beat Moorpark goalie Mike Zemansky with a shot into the right corner of the net 
at the 36-minute, 40-second mark. 
</P>
<P>
