<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shows Canceled: Weekend shows by rock duo Bob Weir &amp; Rob Wasserman and 
country singer Vince Gill were postponed after the newly reopened Raymond 
Theatre in Pasadena was closed by fire marshals Friday because of inadequate 
fire retardant. 
</P>
<P>
The shows were the second and third bookings at the renovated movie house, 
which reopened on Nov. 16. The Raymond marks promoter Gary Folgner's entry into 
the Los Angeles concert market after his success with the Coach House in San 
Juan Capistrano and the Ventura Theatre in Ventura. No new dates for the 
postponed concerts have been announced, but a spokeswoman for Gill said that 
the singer probably won't perform in the area until next spring. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
