<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: RADIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Who'll Take the Rap: A format change may be planned for KDAY-AM (1580), the 
nation's leading rap station, purchased recently by Realtor Fred Sands. 
Although the sale is not yet final, Gary Price, general manager of heavy metal 
station KNAC-FM, which is also owned by Sands, said that a study is being 
conducted to determine what format the powerful station should have. Retaining 
the rap music format is one possibility, Price said. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
