<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BUENA PARK; 
</P>
<P>
NEW RAMPS TO OPEN AHEAD OF SCHEDULE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNDA NATALI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A new on-ramp and off-ramp to the Santa Ana Freeway at Beach Boulevard will 
open this week, eight months ahead of schedule, Caltrans officials have 
announced. 
</P>
<P>
"It is a win-win situation," Caltrans resident engineer Junior Reichert told 
city officials. 
</P>
<P>
"It is eight months ahead of schedule and within budget too." 
</P>
<P>
The northbound ramps are expected to open today and the southbound ramps are 
scheduled to open Dec. 14. 
</P>
<P>
The $4.1-million interchange, which links Beach Boulevard to the Santa Ana 
Freeway, is seen as a crucial link for the Buena Park central business 
district, which depends on Beach Boulevard for access and visibility. 
</P>
<P>
"This is an event we have waited for for a long time," said Fred Sica, director 
of the Buena Park Chamber of Commerce. 
</P>
<P>
Although construction was completed ahead of schedule, getting the project 
started wasn't an easy task. It was mired on the California Department of 
Transportation's eligibility list for more than 20 years and consistently fell 
victim to budget cuts.LYNDA NATALI 
</P>
</TEXT>
