<TEXT>
<P>
Theater Chain Expansion: Despite the slumping economy, Newport Beach-based 
Edwards Theatres says it will continue its $45-million expansion program. 
</P>
<P>
Edwards, one of Southern California's largest theater chains, says it has eight 
multi-screen theaters under construction. Most of the deals were done several 
years ago, according to company Chairman James Edwards Sr. "We're not backing 
off," he said, though he does expect a recession to hurt ticket sales. Among 
the movie houses under construction are theaters in Alhambra, Del Mar, 
Murrieta, La Verne, Ontario and Rancho California. 
</P>
