<TEXT>
<P>
Canada Is in Recession, Government Says: After seven years of robust growth, 
Canada's economy has officially slipped into recession, the government said. 
</P>
<P>
It reported that gross domestic product, a wide measure of economic activity, 
fell for the second consecutive quarter -- Canada's definition of a recession. 
In the July-to-September period, the economy contracted at an annualized rate 
of 1%. In the second quarter, output declined at a 1.2% rate. Economists said 
the downturn is mild, however, and, barring a Persian Gulf war and further oil 
price increases, should end sometime next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
