<TEXT>
<P>
Sunwest Bank Awarded $5.8 Million: Sunwest Bank, a small subsidiary of West 
Coast Bancorp, was awarded $5.8 million in a suit against Lloyd's of London for 
breach of its insurance contract. 
</P>
<P>
The award by a federal jury includes punitive damages of $2.5 million against 
Lloyd's. Sunwest, a five-branch bank based in Orange County, sued in 1986 after 
Lloyd's rejected a $1.3-million insurance claim. (Case No. 86-7190. Verdict on 
Nov. 26, 1990.) 
</P>
