<TEXT>
<P>
Tokheim Plans to Close Tennessee Plant: Ft. Wayne, Ind.-based Tokheim Corp., a 
major manufacturer of service station gasoline pumps, will close its Newbern, 
Tenn., assembly plant to reduce manufacturing costs. 
</P>
<P>
Operations at the Tennessee plant, which employs 308, will be folded into the 
Ft. Wayne fabrication and machining plant by late summer of 1991. Tokheim 
officials said a new contract with members of United Auto Workers at the Ft. 
Wayne factory was a main factor in their decision to relocate to northeastern 
Indiana. 
</P>
