<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN COURT: A SUMMARY OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA-RELATED BUSINESS LITIGATION 
DEVELOPMENTS DURING THE PAST WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orange County Man Pleads Guilty: An Orange County man pleaded guilty to charges 
stemming from a scheme to defraud financial institutions across the country of 
millions of dollars by persuading them to finance real estate developments in 
Arizona and California. 
</P>
<P>
John M. Couglan Sr., 75, the last of three defendants to plead guilty, 
conducted the scheme in 1986 through two companies, Eagle Bonds and Insurance 
Brokers Inc. and California Pacific Construction Co. E. F. Hutton Life 
Insurance Co. was defrauded of $5.5 million, and East Baton Rouge Retirement 
System lost $1.02 million. (Case No. 90-548. Plea Entered Nov. 26, 1990.) 
</P>
