<TEXT>
<P>
Gillette Threatens To Close Plant: The consumer products firm is threatening to 
close the world's largest razor blade plant if Boston bans ozone-depleting 
chemicals. 
</P>
<P>
The city is considering outlawing chemicals that deplete the ozone layer 
protecting the Earth from damaging rays from the sun. Gillette Vice Chairman 
Joseph E. Mullaney said the ban would put the company at a competitive 
disadvantage, and if the bill is adopted, Gillette will close its South Boston 
plant next year. The plant employs 3,100. 
</P>
