<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
REAL MOTHER JOLTS ED BEGLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ed Begley Jr., the father in television's "Parenthood," says when he applied 
for his driver's license at 16 he learned who his real mother was from his 
birth certificate. 
</P>
<P>
Begley, 41, said in the Dec. 8 issue of TV Guide that it took him some time to 
adjust to the fact his father's first wife was not his mother, as he had 
assumed. 
</P>
<P>
"It's pretty strange when you think one woman is your mother and you find out 
it's another woman," he said. "That lady who used to bring you Lincoln Logs? 
Yeah, I remember her. Well, for good reason, son. That's your mom." 
</P>
<P>
Begley said he gets along great with his mother, whom he knew as a family 
friend during his childhood. 
</P>
<P>
The name of the woman was not revealed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
